19:30.778 --> 19:34.869
We do not gutter...

19:34.912 --> 19:37.350
into the ashes of history.

19:37.393 --> 19:40.222
We are the originators
of history.

19:40.266 --> 19:41.963
This!

19:42.006 --> 19:44.095
This is not an end!

19:45.401 --> 19:47.229
This is a beginning!

19:47.273 --> 19:50.406
Who decides that you're over?

19:51.190 --> 19:54.584
Who decides that
you've gone far enough?

19:54.628 --> 19:57.805
These small, simple, men?

19:57.848 --> 20:00.111
They know nothing
of greatness.

20:00.155 --> 20:02.766
How could they possibly
appreciate

20:02.810 --> 20:05.552
a true vision such as yours?

20:05.595 --> 20:08.250
All they can do is fear it.

20:09.686 --> 20:12.385
Your detractors.

20:12.428 --> 20:14.213
What are they?

20:16.432 --> 20:20.567
Sightless worms
squirming in the syrup

20:20.610 --> 20:23.222
of a decomposing culture.

20:23.265 --> 20:26.573
You are the brightest star

20:26.616 --> 20:28.444
in the sky, Sonny.

20:28.488 --> 20:31.491
And a blind maggot
does not stop

20:31.534 --> 20:33.884
the sun from shining.

20:33.928 --> 20:37.105
Will you now let them
snuff you out

20:37.148 --> 20:40.804
on the eve of your
greatest triumph?

20:40.848 --> 20:44.547
We don't need permission.

20:44.591 --> 20:48.203
We don't need anyone.

20:48.247 --> 20:52.338
Now you pull up
your golden britches

20:52.381 --> 20:56.429
and you show the world what
you are damn well made of.

20:56.472 --> 20:59.432
The show will go on!

20:59.475 --> 21:02.609
all: Orcus! Orcus!

21:02.652 --> 21:06.569
Orcus! Orcus! Orcus!

21:07.744 --> 21:10.573
- You get me.

21:10.617 --> 21:13.141
You understand.

21:14.795 --> 21:17.406
You understand.

21:18.842 --> 21:21.323
The show...

21:21.367 --> 21:22.803
will...

21:22.846 --> 21:25.109
go on!

21:25.153 --> 21:27.460
It will!
[muffled yelp]

21:31.377 --> 21:32.378
[laughs]

21:34.467 --> 21:37.034
- ♪ In your Easter bonnet

21:37.078 --> 21:40.734
♪ With all the frills
upon it ♪

21:40.777 --> 21:45.216
♪ You'll be
the grandest lady ♪

21:45.260 --> 21:49.525
♪ In the Easter chorus

21:51.962 --> 21:54.356
- Can you take our picture?

21:54.400 --> 21:58.142
- ♪ And when
they look you over ♪

21:58.186 --> 22:02.712
♪ I'll be
the proudest fellow ♪

22:02.756 --> 22:06.977
♪ In the Easter parade

22:07.021 --> 22:11.547
♪ On the avenue

22:11.591 --> 22:13.462
♪ Fifth avenue

22:13.506 --> 22:15.464
- Thanks!

22:15.508 --> 22:17.814
- ♪ The photographers
will snap us ♪

22:17.858 --> 22:19.642
- Here, we'll take one for you.

22:19.686 --> 22:22.993
- ♪ And you'll find that
you're in the rotogravure ♪

22:23.037 --> 22:25.126
- Smile.

22:25.169 --> 22:28.999
- ♪ Oh, I could write
a sonnet ♪

22:29.043 --> 22:30.827
♪ About your evening bonnet

22:30.871 --> 22:32.829
- Don't shake it.

22:33.613 --> 22:37.791
- ♪ And of the girl
I'm taking ♪

22:37.834 --> 22:41.360
♪ To the Easter parade

22:42.796 --> 22:45.189
- Hey, Rita.
- Hey, McCarthy.

22:45.233 --> 22:46.974
What's the name?
- Bianchi.

22:47.017 --> 22:48.541
She's still
in pretrial detention.

22:48.584 --> 22:50.804
Should be block C.
- Well, shit.

22:50.847 --> 22:52.545
Bianchi, you said?
- Yeah.

22:52.588 --> 22:54.634
- Well, that ain't good.

22:54.677 --> 22:57.332
- What?
- Uh...

22:57.376 --> 23:00.640
- I hate to be the bear
of bad news.

23:00.683 --> 23:02.772
- Bearer.
- What?

23:02.816 --> 23:05.993
- It's the "bearer."

23:06.036 --> 23:08.038
"Bearer of bad--"
Never mind.

23:08.082 --> 23:09.257
Ugh.
What is it?

23:09.300 --> 23:11.999
- Well, uh, about Bianchi,

23:12.042 --> 23:13.870
she was--

23:13.914 --> 23:16.395
I don't know how to say this.
You weren't related, were you?

23:16.438 --> 23:17.961
- Go on.

23:18.005 --> 23:19.833
- You are not gonna believe--

23:19.876 --> 23:22.488
I'm not even sure how
such a thing could happen.

23:22.531 --> 23:25.055
Uh, but she was.

23:25.099 --> 23:26.709
Oh, hell,
I'm just gonna say it.

23:28.145 --> 23:31.105
[ominous music]

23:31.148 --> 23:35.283
♪

23:35.326 --> 23:37.720
- Hello, my lovely.

23:40.636 --> 23:42.551
My autumn bloom.

23:44.510 --> 23:47.556
Oh, what, are you not
talking to me now then?

23:47.600 --> 23:49.036
Really?

23:49.732 --> 23:53.432
But you were so loquacious
the last time we met.

23:54.520 --> 23:58.088
By the way,
that was most unkind.

23:59.089 --> 24:02.615
Business with
the knitting needles.

24:03.920 --> 24:05.574
[laughing]

24:06.923 --> 24:09.143
[maniacal cackling]

24:15.715 --> 24:17.760
Most unkind.

24:18.674 --> 24:23.026
Trapping me in this too,
too solid flesh.

24:23.766 --> 24:26.247
And what's a life sentence
to you, eh?

24:26.290 --> 24:28.510
Barely a slap on the wrist.

24:28.554 --> 24:33.776
Still, nobody to blame
but myself I suppose.

24:37.127 --> 24:40.000
Ugh, fine.

24:40.043 --> 24:42.524
I'll leave you
to your knitting.

24:44.047 --> 24:45.919
Oh!

24:45.962 --> 24:47.442
One thing before I leave.

24:47.486 --> 24:51.272
Um, I did want to send
a message to your sisters.

24:51.315 --> 24:55.145
[ominous music]

24:55.189 --> 24:57.408
- I think...

24:57.452 --> 25:00.716
they will have
a message for you.

25:01.674 --> 25:03.284
Soon.

25:03.327 --> 25:06.417
- Hello.
There she is!

25:06.461 --> 25:07.593
Hello!

25:07.636 --> 25:10.030
No, but don't you see,
young lady?

25:10.073 --> 25:13.163
I'm free now.
Hm-hm-hm-hm.

25:13.816 --> 25:17.211
My strength is coming back,
spring is in the air,

25:17.254 --> 25:20.475
and tonight,
most special of nights,

25:20.519 --> 25:24.131
I'm going to crush into powder
the hopes and dreams

25:24.174 --> 25:27.351
of millions of innocent souls.

25:28.831 --> 25:30.833
Again!

25:30.877 --> 25:34.794
And there's nothing
any of you can do to stop me.

25:34.837 --> 25:37.797
But that's not the message.

25:39.146 --> 25:43.150
The message, young lady...

25:43.193 --> 25:45.326
is you.

25:45.369 --> 25:52.594
♪

26:01.037 --> 26:03.300
[needles clacking]

26:03.344 --> 26:07.130
- [groans]

26:07.174 --> 26:09.524
Ahh!
Ahhh!

26:12.353 --> 26:15.835
[screaming]

26:15.878 --> 26:17.880
[plopping]

26:20.970 --> 26:22.624
- Decapitated?

26:22.668 --> 26:24.583
As in...

26:30.458 --> 26:32.373
Well, all right then.

26:32.416 --> 26:33.679
- Oh, wait.
Hold up, McCarthy.

26:33.722 --> 26:35.028
This says there's
something here for you.

26:35.071 --> 26:37.421
- For me?

26:37.465 --> 26:39.598
Her belongings.

26:39.641 --> 26:42.470
- Seriously?
- Left them in your care.

26:49.999 --> 26:53.307
[ominous music]

26:53.350 --> 26:55.483
♪

26:55.526 --> 26:58.051
- Wait, wait, wait.
There's something more.

26:58.094 --> 26:59.182
- And what's this?

26:59.226 --> 27:01.620
- That's...her.

27:09.497 --> 27:11.412
- I mean, I gotta tell ya,
I have been down

27:11.455 --> 27:13.544
some dark alleys
of addiction town,

27:13.588 --> 27:15.329
but I ain't never seen
nothing like that.

27:15.372 --> 27:16.722
What with the whipped cream?
She must have been

27:16.765 --> 27:18.506
going through two,
three cases at a time.

27:18.549 --> 27:20.203
[gasps]
Who are you?

27:20.247 --> 27:23.293
Passing up stuff like this.
That's what I'm talking about.

27:23.337 --> 27:25.687
- Whipped cream
is a gateway treat, Nick.

27:25.731 --> 27:28.298
It leads to more decadent
confections.

27:28.342 --> 27:30.039
And do you really think
another bottle

27:30.083 --> 27:32.128
of ass whoop
is a good idea?

27:32.172 --> 27:34.435
- No, I don't, Hap.

27:37.046 --> 27:39.832
- The strangest thing happened
back there at the hospital.

27:39.875 --> 27:41.834
- I was just--
- I don't know if it was

27:41.877 --> 27:45.533
the drugs
or that shit they gave me.

27:47.013 --> 27:49.842
I think I saw Happy.

27:49.885 --> 27:52.366
- Holy moly macaroni,
I knew it!

27:52.409 --> 27:54.716
- Happy?
- Hailey's imaginary friend.

27:54.760 --> 27:56.762
- Oh, Amanda, I'm here.
Right here.

27:56.805 --> 27:58.328
Can you see me?
- Um, yeah.

27:58.372 --> 27:59.765
I--I think if you were
to tell anybody that,

27:59.808 --> 28:01.418
they'd think you were a little
[cuckoo whistling].

28:01.462 --> 28:03.856
- I only know him
from Hailey's drawings,

28:03.899 --> 28:06.989
and from the way she used
to talk about him.

28:07.033 --> 28:09.035
The horn.

28:10.079 --> 28:11.820
The sweet smile.

28:11.864 --> 28:14.214
[soft music]

28:14.257 --> 28:18.218
A happy horse-horse.

28:18.261 --> 28:21.395
I remember the first time
she sang that song.

28:22.309 --> 28:24.746
She was 4 3/4

28:24.790 --> 28:27.488
and she asked me
where her dad was.

28:27.531 --> 28:30.621
I told her the truth,
that I had no idea.

28:30.665 --> 28:32.841
She created Happy the next day.

28:34.364 --> 28:35.844
'Cause of you I suppose.

28:35.888 --> 28:37.498
- Tell her, Nick.
Go on.

28:37.541 --> 28:39.848
Tell her you see me, too.

28:41.241 --> 28:43.983
- Amanda...

28:44.026 --> 28:46.507
- Yeah?

28:46.550 --> 28:48.901
- Come on, Nick!
Tell her!

28:52.687 --> 28:54.036
- I just hope that
he's with her right now,

28:54.080 --> 28:55.777
telling her that everything
is gonna be all right,

28:55.821 --> 28:59.476
telling her that we're
coming for her because we are.

29:00.564 --> 29:02.305
- I hope so, too.

29:02.349 --> 29:04.743
[phone rings]

29:09.269 --> 29:10.487
- Hello.

29:10.531 --> 29:12.011
- Mrs. Hansen?
- Yes?

29:12.054 --> 29:13.839
- This is Sister Lee
from St. Melanie's.

29:13.882 --> 29:15.362
- Sister Lee?

29:15.405 --> 29:17.233
- I wanted you to know
that Hailey showed up here.

29:17.277 --> 29:18.539
- Hailey's at school.

29:18.582 --> 29:20.019
- She's scared
but she's safe.

29:20.062 --> 29:22.021
You should come
and pick her up.

29:35.208 --> 29:38.428
- Hey, can I cash that in?

29:38.472 --> 29:41.388
[ominous music]

29:41.431 --> 29:48.699
♪

29:51.137 --> 29:54.314
Um...

29:54.357 --> 29:58.144
Where are you going?

29:58.187 --> 30:01.147
[carnival music]

30:01.190 --> 30:08.458
♪

30:20.993 --> 30:22.646
[whispered voices]

30:34.528 --> 30:36.660
- Try not to worry, Amanda.
We'll find her.

30:37.618 --> 30:39.272
Was it true what you said?

30:39.315 --> 30:42.014
That Hailey invented me
because Nick wasn't there?

30:42.057 --> 30:43.929
Maybe I was always
meant to find him.

30:43.972 --> 30:45.844
Maybe that was my purpose.

30:45.887 --> 30:48.847
[ominous music]

30:48.890 --> 30:56.115
♪

31:00.641 --> 31:03.426
- ♪ Here comes
Peter Cottontail ♪

31:03.470 --> 31:06.081
♪ Hopping down
the bunny trail ♪

31:06.125 --> 31:10.433
♪ Hippity hoppin',
Easter's on its way ♪

31:10.477 --> 31:13.306
♪ Bringing every girl and boy

31:13.349 --> 31:16.178
♪ Baskets full
of Easter toys ♪

31:16.222 --> 31:19.747
♪ Making your Easter
bright and guy ♪

31:19.790 --> 31:23.185
♪ He's got jelly beans
for Tommy ♪

31:23.229 --> 31:26.145
♪ Colored eggs for Sister Sue

31:26.188 --> 31:27.755
[screaming]

31:34.893 --> 31:36.677
- I thought she'd never stop.

31:36.720 --> 31:39.680
[dramatic music]

31:39.723 --> 31:43.945
♪

31:43.989 --> 31:47.644
- I know.
What's a boy to do?

31:47.688 --> 31:49.559
- I got ideas.

31:50.865 --> 31:54.782
- But none of them really
hit the spot, now do they?

31:56.958 --> 31:58.917
You can't kill me.

31:58.960 --> 32:01.571
Then you won't find her.

32:01.615 --> 32:03.965
You can't torture me.

32:04.009 --> 32:06.837
What would be the point?

32:06.881 --> 32:08.796
- Fun?

32:08.839 --> 32:10.929
- [giggling]

32:10.972 --> 32:13.148
Maybe for both of us.

32:13.192 --> 32:14.845
But it wouldn't
get you any closer

32:14.889 --> 32:17.631
to your little whippersnapper,
now would it?

32:18.545 --> 32:22.375
- We both know this doesn't end
until one of us is dead.

32:23.942 --> 32:25.726
- Absolutely.

32:27.075 --> 32:29.991
But there are much worse
things than dead.

32:30.035 --> 32:31.514
- Nick!
- Yeah, sweetie?

32:31.558 --> 32:33.864
- Amanda, no!
- Who the fuck is this?

32:33.908 --> 32:36.563
- This...

32:36.606 --> 32:39.174
is the guy
I was telling you about.

32:39.218 --> 32:40.828
- I'm blushing.

32:41.481 --> 32:43.700
Whatever he told you...

32:43.744 --> 32:44.875
all true.

32:44.919 --> 32:46.529
- I have a question, Nick.

32:46.573 --> 32:49.054
Why is this motherfucker
not tied up to a chair

32:49.097 --> 32:51.186
with his
balls in a vice?

32:54.755 --> 32:56.017
- Yeah, about that...

32:56.061 --> 32:57.627
- What the fuck is up
with you two?

32:57.671 --> 32:59.151
- We're gonna listen
to what he has to say.

32:59.194 --> 33:00.587
- Really?
Okay, sure.

33:00.630 --> 33:02.676
I'm all ears.

33:02.719 --> 33:04.373
- Ugh.

33:07.811 --> 33:09.944
- Hyah!
Well?

33:09.988 --> 33:11.815
I'm listening!

33:13.513 --> 33:14.688
Ah!

33:14.731 --> 33:16.559
I'm listening!

33:16.603 --> 33:19.823
[grunting]

33:19.867 --> 33:23.784
♪

33:23.827 --> 33:26.526
[exhausted breathing]

33:27.353 --> 33:29.572
- It's cathartic.
- Ugh...

33:29.616 --> 33:31.270
- Honey.

33:32.097 --> 33:33.489
I know you wanna kill him,
so do I,

33:33.533 --> 33:36.144
but he knows where Hailey is.

33:36.188 --> 33:38.625
And you gotta believe me,

33:38.668 --> 33:42.368
he ain't telling,
no matter what we do.

33:42.411 --> 33:44.848
Come on.
Come on, now.

33:44.892 --> 33:46.459
Atta girl.

33:50.463 --> 33:52.421
- I'm sure you enjoyed that.

33:52.465 --> 33:53.640
- I did.

33:54.728 --> 33:57.383
- Good.
Now, can we get on with it?

33:57.426 --> 33:59.254
- Oh!
- Hey, come on.

33:59.298 --> 34:01.213
She's still alive.

34:01.256 --> 34:03.215
She's still alive.

34:03.258 --> 34:06.392
Killing her would be too easy.
He has a plan.

34:06.435 --> 34:08.916
And I think he's had it
for a long time.

34:21.233 --> 34:23.974
- Make yourselves comfortable.

34:24.018 --> 34:26.499
We've got some time to kill.

34:27.891 --> 34:31.156
- [whispering]
I think I broke my hand.

34:44.995 --> 34:46.214
- [struggling]

34:46.258 --> 34:49.783
- Assunta Bianchi
sent you here.

34:49.826 --> 34:50.784
Why?

34:50.827 --> 34:52.525
- Fuck her.

35:01.360 --> 35:05.451
I don't know why
she sent me here.

35:05.494 --> 35:07.279
So let's start
with you bitches

35:07.322 --> 35:09.281
telling me
who the hell you are.

35:09.324 --> 35:16.244
♪

35:24.034 --> 35:27.212
[choking, coughing]

35:28.038 --> 35:30.215
- Keith McCarthy.

35:32.434 --> 35:34.175
A cop's daughter.

35:34.219 --> 35:37.526
I wonder,
what did he teach?

35:37.570 --> 35:40.138
- How to clean and load a .45.

35:40.181 --> 35:42.227
And if you don't take his name
out of your mouth,

35:42.270 --> 35:45.230
I'll show you
something else he taught me.

35:45.273 --> 35:47.667
- He didn't teach you
to be just.

35:49.234 --> 35:51.105
We've seen your record.

35:52.019 --> 35:55.283
You lied and cheated
every chance you could.

35:55.327 --> 35:57.198
You were a disgrace
to everything

35:57.242 --> 35:59.809
your father stood for.

35:59.853 --> 36:02.160
- Maybe I didn't know what
being a cop meant

36:02.203 --> 36:03.291
until I lost my badge.

36:03.335 --> 36:05.424
Is that what you want to hear?

36:11.386 --> 36:14.607
- Assunta told you about Orcus.

36:16.783 --> 36:18.263
- Yeah.

36:19.438 --> 36:21.875
And I guess I believe her.
Now the fuck what?

36:23.442 --> 36:25.922
- You've seen evil.

36:27.141 --> 36:30.057
Did you ever stop to wonder
where it comes from?

36:30.797 --> 36:32.668
Do you think the horror
and brutality

36:32.712 --> 36:35.018
of this world is random?

36:36.281 --> 36:38.196
- People generally suck

36:38.239 --> 36:40.589
is how I put it.

36:48.031 --> 36:51.209
- The world is polluted
by old gods.

36:51.252 --> 36:54.647
Sick, lingering, old Gods.

36:54.690 --> 36:57.519
Hanging on to shreds of belief

36:57.563 --> 37:01.001
like a pox festering
in dark corners.

37:01.828 --> 37:04.961
Shrinking from the sterile
light of day.

37:05.005 --> 37:09.401
Looking for fresh,
unvaccinated cells.

37:09.444 --> 37:12.055
Preying on weak souls.

37:13.056 --> 37:14.493
Like yours.

37:14.536 --> 37:16.103
- [hyperventilating]

37:16.146 --> 37:18.497
[screaming]

37:25.504 --> 37:28.898
- We are bound to cleanse them
from this world.

37:34.382 --> 37:37.037
And now you are bound to us.

37:38.343 --> 37:41.346
- [whimpering]

37:42.782 --> 37:46.133
- Welcome to the Blue Feather,
Merry McCarthy.

37:48.440 --> 37:50.833
You're one of us now.

37:52.357 --> 37:55.011
[percussive music]

37:55.055 --> 37:58.885
[cheers and applause]

37:58.928 --> 38:01.279
- [laughing]

38:01.322 --> 38:04.107
- Sonny!
[laughing]

38:04.151 --> 38:05.283
So serious.

38:05.326 --> 38:06.893
What's on your mind?

38:06.936 --> 38:08.329
- Easter.

38:08.373 --> 38:10.984
The joy of candy, colors,

38:11.027 --> 38:12.942
creativity and costuming.

38:12.986 --> 38:15.380
A season unlike any other,
but don't be fooled

38:15.423 --> 38:18.383
by these glorious pastels.

38:18.426 --> 38:21.386
Because we are under attack.

38:21.429 --> 38:23.649
There are those
that would crack our eggs,

38:23.692 --> 38:25.912
that would bukakke our baskets,

38:25.955 --> 38:28.697
poison our puddings.

38:28.741 --> 38:32.701
But tonight I say J'accuse!

38:32.745 --> 38:36.226
We will not be intimidated
by a little bee in our bonnet.

38:36.270 --> 38:40.230
No, we will fight back
and stand strong.

38:40.274 --> 38:43.059
Easter Strong.

38:43.103 --> 38:44.365
Trademark pending.

38:44.409 --> 38:46.106
- Wasn't that magnificent?
Are you moved?

38:46.149 --> 38:48.064
I was moved, I know something
certainly moved.

38:48.108 --> 38:50.066
- Back off, rent boy.

38:50.110 --> 38:51.764
- I'm so sorry, Sunshine.

38:51.807 --> 38:54.462
Any comment about last
night's big announcement?

38:54.506 --> 38:57.247
- I was talking to Tara.

38:57.291 --> 38:59.424
Wait, you're not Tara.

38:59.467 --> 39:00.860
- I wanna know about the big
announcement

39:00.903 --> 39:02.644
that your show
is being canceled.

39:02.688 --> 39:04.951
Everyone is saying that your
career is deader

39:04.994 --> 39:06.213
than Sharon Tate's--

39:06.256 --> 39:08.998
- I'm totally digging
your contouring today,

39:09.042 --> 39:10.478
B-T-dubs.

39:10.522 --> 39:12.175
- Canceled?
- Can--

39:12.219 --> 39:13.742
- Canceled?
[laughs]

39:13.786 --> 39:17.572
Jesus was canceled and
that didn't stop him, did it?

39:17.616 --> 39:20.575
- But what about
the bunny, Sonny?

39:20.619 --> 39:22.577
- [whistles]

39:22.621 --> 39:26.146
I have no idea
what you're talk--oh.

39:26.189 --> 39:27.974
That bunny.

39:28.017 --> 39:31.586
I do think my--my little
SunDrops have had quite enough

39:31.630 --> 39:33.196
of the nightmares
about a little

39:33.240 --> 39:36.286
crazy animal that the French
put in stew.

39:36.330 --> 39:39.202
But if he comes to my show,

39:39.246 --> 39:40.682
on my stage,

39:40.726 --> 39:43.119
on this special day...

39:43.163 --> 39:44.947
[chuckles]

39:44.991 --> 39:47.515
I'll be waiting.

39:47.559 --> 39:51.040
The show must go on!
[maniacal laughter]

39:53.303 --> 39:55.480
[horns honking]

39:58.613 --> 40:01.399
- What are some fun car games
to pass the time?

40:01.442 --> 40:03.618
Hm?

40:03.662 --> 40:05.707
Oh, I know.
Let's play, Would You Rather.

40:05.751 --> 40:06.926
- That's a low blow.

40:06.969 --> 40:08.710
Everyone loves
Would You Rather.

40:08.754 --> 40:10.625
- You can't take the tunnel
this time of night, Nick.

40:10.669 --> 40:12.105
- God help me I need a drink.

40:12.148 --> 40:14.324
- Would you rather have gone
your whole life

40:14.368 --> 40:17.284
without ever knowing
about Hailey but guaranteeing

40:17.327 --> 40:19.852
that she's safe, or...

40:19.895 --> 40:21.419
is all of this worth it

40:21.462 --> 40:22.855
just to play daddy
for a few months?

40:22.898 --> 40:25.640
- Would you rather have
my fist down your throat

40:25.684 --> 40:26.989
or up your ass?

40:27.033 --> 40:28.817
- Whoa, Amanda's
really good at this.

40:28.861 --> 40:32.691
- And I took you for just
another TV mom in distress.

40:32.734 --> 40:34.823
I like her, Sax.

40:34.867 --> 40:37.130
You punched way above
your weight class

40:37.173 --> 40:40.046
with thissss...

40:40.089 --> 40:41.308
bitch.

40:41.351 --> 40:43.441
- Enjoy it while you can,
motherfucker.

40:43.484 --> 40:45.181
It ain't gonna last.

40:45.225 --> 40:46.487
- Nothing good ever does.

40:46.531 --> 40:47.923
- Should have taken
the Queensboro.

40:47.967 --> 40:50.665
- Let's ventilate this
son a female dog.

40:50.709 --> 40:52.537
I found you, Nick.
We can find Hailey.

40:52.580 --> 40:55.148
- Hi, it's Hailey. Sorry
I can't answer the phone--

40:57.193 --> 41:00.153
- Oh, I have another game.
Hm?

41:00.196 --> 41:02.895
I spy with my little eye

41:02.938 --> 41:05.245
the inside of your brain.

41:05.288 --> 41:08.509
Seductive, isn't it?
The "what's nexts,"

41:08.553 --> 41:10.032
the "what ifs."

41:10.076 --> 41:12.644
Imagination does
half my work for me.

41:12.687 --> 41:14.080
- Don't listen to him.
- Oh, he's right.

41:14.123 --> 41:16.691
Don't listen to me.
What do I know?

41:16.735 --> 41:19.477
Except exactly where Hailey is.

41:19.520 --> 41:21.522
Hey, is your seatbelt on?
- Mm-hmm.

41:21.566 --> 41:23.698
[tires screeching]

41:23.742 --> 41:25.265
[thunk]

41:26.875 --> 41:29.356
- You think you're
such an expert on pain?

41:29.399 --> 41:31.576
When we're done with
whatever the fuck this is

41:31.619 --> 41:33.229
I am gonna teach you
things that--

41:33.273 --> 41:34.753
- Don't be boring.

41:34.796 --> 41:38.931
When I am done with whatever
this is that I am doing,

41:38.974 --> 41:41.499
you will be too busy shopping
for razorblades

41:41.542 --> 41:45.851
and drawing a warm bubble bath
to even think about me.

41:45.894 --> 41:49.071
[ominous music]

41:49.115 --> 41:56.122
♪

42:16.359 --> 42:18.710
[horns honking]

42:20.320 --> 42:22.148
[knocking]

42:32.506 --> 42:34.247
- Hello, poppet.

42:35.335 --> 42:38.381
May I come in?
- What do you want?

42:41.428 --> 42:44.649
- You know who I am?
- You were at the diner.

42:46.868 --> 42:49.958
- And you're not afraid of me?

42:50.002 --> 42:53.309
- I know who runs the show,
and it's not you.

42:56.051 --> 42:57.531
- Hm.

42:57.575 --> 43:00.142
Well said.

43:00.186 --> 43:02.623
For what it's worth,
I was looking forward

43:02.667 --> 43:04.146
to meeting you.

43:04.190 --> 43:07.106
But no,
I understand your hesitancy.

43:08.194 --> 43:11.980
Trust is difficult
to come by these days.

43:12.024 --> 43:15.201
Best not to dole it out
willy-nilly.

43:22.382 --> 43:24.210
[sighs]

43:24.253 --> 43:26.299
Oh, God no.

43:27.735 --> 43:30.259
Oh, no.
This doesn't suit you at all.

43:31.652 --> 43:32.871
Does it?

43:32.914 --> 43:36.831
Some ghastly façade
of childhood.

43:36.875 --> 43:38.964
Life is so much more
complicated

43:39.007 --> 43:41.880
than whatever mask
we put on it.

43:43.316 --> 43:45.013
We both know that.

43:46.145 --> 43:47.363
Don't we?

43:57.722 --> 44:00.681
Ah!
Bugger me.

44:00.725 --> 44:02.422
That's better.

44:03.728 --> 44:06.992
Well, first
I have to admit that

44:07.035 --> 44:10.082
I didn't think you were capable
of the task at hand.

44:11.126 --> 44:13.781
But true courage, Hailey,

44:13.825 --> 44:16.392
true courage...

44:16.436 --> 44:19.439
can't be forged...

44:19.482 --> 44:21.484
in either sense of the word.

44:22.964 --> 44:26.359
It lives in you or it doesn't.

44:27.969 --> 44:30.406
And when I look at you,

44:30.450 --> 44:32.931
I see a young woman

44:32.974 --> 44:35.716
who's capable of so much more

44:35.760 --> 44:38.327
than she ever thought possible.

44:40.939 --> 44:42.854
That's all I got to say.

44:42.897 --> 44:44.943
Really.

44:45.813 --> 44:48.337
You know, Hailey.

44:49.121 --> 44:51.210
You can never get back

44:51.253 --> 44:53.734
what was stolen from you.

44:53.778 --> 44:55.736
It's long gone.

44:55.780 --> 45:00.567
But you can make
the world more just--

45:00.610 --> 45:02.743
no, not just.

45:02.787 --> 45:05.920
More...

45:05.964 --> 45:07.922
More correct.

45:07.966 --> 45:10.882
And I believe you will.

45:13.667 --> 45:15.582
Enjoy your supper.

45:20.543 --> 45:27.594
♪

45:29.683 --> 45:33.121
- Not gonna sugar coat this.
We're in the shit right now.

45:33.165 --> 45:36.298
I got no idea what he has
in mind for us but I know this:

45:36.342 --> 45:41.434
He wants it too bad.
He's gonna make a mistake.

45:41.477 --> 45:44.480
And when he does...

45:44.524 --> 45:46.308
You trust me, Amanda?

45:46.352 --> 45:48.180
- I do.

46:12.030 --> 46:14.075
- If you wouldn't mind
doing the honors?

46:14.119 --> 46:16.251
- You want me to inject him?

46:16.295 --> 46:17.557
- Yes.

46:17.600 --> 46:18.950
- What is it?

46:18.993 --> 46:21.866
- What if I told you
that it was poison?

46:22.736 --> 46:27.306
Kill him and you get your
precious little apple back.

46:27.349 --> 46:28.481
Would you do it?

46:28.524 --> 46:30.918
- You're god damn right
she would.

46:30.962 --> 46:33.138
- Don't worry
about alcohol wipes.

46:33.181 --> 46:35.531
His body produces it naturally.

46:46.325 --> 46:49.023
- We were terrible
for each other.

46:51.504 --> 46:53.636
- The worst.

46:53.680 --> 46:56.291
- In the buttocks, please.

46:57.118 --> 46:59.120
together: Seriously?

46:59.164 --> 47:02.428
[electric guitar]

47:02.471 --> 47:09.522
♪

47:11.611 --> 47:14.875
- ♪ Yo-ho!

47:14.919 --> 47:17.225
- I got your back.
- Me too, buddy.

47:17.269 --> 47:19.880
- ♪ Yo-ho!

47:19.924 --> 47:22.230
♪ Yo-ho!

47:22.274 --> 47:26.191
♪ There goes my gun
- ♪ My gun

47:26.234 --> 47:29.020
- ♪ There goes my gun
